        <tr>
          <th scope="row" rowspan="4">
                  Commitment to Pupils and Pupil Learning
                </th>
          <td class="num">1</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers demonstrate commitment to the well-being and
                  development of all pupils.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should see in class observation
                </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="num">2</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers are dedicated in their efforts to teach and support
                  pupil learning and achievement.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should see in class observation
                </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="num">3</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers treat all pupils equitably and with respect.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should see in class observation
                </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="num">4</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers provide an environment for learning that encourages
                  pupils to be problem solvers, decision makers, lifelong
                  learners, and contributing members of a changing society.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should see in class observation
                </td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
          <th scope="row" rowspan="4">Professional Knowledge</th>
          <td class="num">5</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers know their subject matter, the Ontario curriculum,
                  and educationrelated legislation.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should see in class observation
                </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="num">6</td>
          <td>
                  Teachers know a variety of effective teaching and assessment
                  practices
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should see in class observation
                </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="num">7</td>
          <td>
                  Teachers know a variety of effective classroom management
                  strategies
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should see in class observation
                </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="num">8</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers know how pupils learn and the factors that influence
                  pupil learning and achievement.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should see in class observation
                </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" rowspan="5">Teaching Practice</th>
          <td class="num">9</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers use their professional knowledge and understanding of
                  pupils, curriculum, legislation, teaching practices, and
                  classroom management
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should see in class observation
                </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="num">10</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers communicate effectively with pupils, parents, and
                  colleagues.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should see in class observation
                </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="num">11</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers conduct ongoing assessment of pupils’ progress,
                  evaluate their achievement, and report results to pupils and
                  their parents regularly.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">Post observation discussion</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="num">12</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers adapt and refine their teaching practices through
                  continuous learning and reflection, using a variety of sources
                  and resources.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should be in your Annual Learning Plan
                </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="num">13</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers use appropriate technology in their teaching
                  practices and related professional responsibilities.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should see in class observation
                </td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
          <th scope="row" rowspan="2">Leadership and Community</th>

          <td class="num">14</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers collaborate with other teachers and school colleagues
                  to create and sustain learning communities in their classrooms
                  and in their schools.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">Post observation discussion</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="num">15</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers work with professionals, parents, and members of the
                  community to enhance pupil learning, pupil achievement, and
                  school programs.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">Post observation discussion</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">Ongoing Professional Learning</th>
          <td class="num">16</td>
          <td class="comp">
                  Teachers engage in ongoing professional learning and apply it
                  to improve their teaching practices.
                </td>
          <td class="none speech-bubble">
                  Should be in your Annual Learning Plan
                </td>
        </tr>
